[metadata]
Name:Fecundity + Vampire Nighthawk event-assertion showcase
Goal:Win
Turns:4
Difficulty:Easy
Description:A showcase for the event-backed assertion DSL — one combat that triggers THREE different event kinds at once. P0 controls Fecundity ("Whenever a creature dies, that creature's controller may draw a card") and Vampire Nighthawk (2/3 flying, deathtouch, lifelink). P1, at 4 life, defends with a 2/2 flying Wind Drake. When P0 attacks with Nighthawk, P1 blocks with Wind Drake (it cannot let the flier through at 4 life). Deathtouch makes Nighthawk's 2 combat damage lethal, so Wind Drake dies (CR 702.2 / 510.1c); Fecundity's "a creature dies" trigger (CR 603.6) fires and Wind Drake's controller draws; and Nighthawk's lifelink (CR 702.15) gains P0 2 life from that same combat damage. The [assertions] section names all three new event kinds — a creature died, a trigger fired, and life was gained.

HOW TO RUN / VERIFY: watch it play out interactively with
  mtg tui --start-state test_puzzles/fecundity_nighthawk_event_showcase.pzl --p1 heuristic --p2 heuristic --seed 42 -v 2 --no-color-logs
The live log prints "Wind Drake ... dies from combat damage", "Trigger: Fecundity ...", and P0's life climbing from 15 to 17 (lifelink). NOTE: the bulk `[assertions]` evaluator (make puzzle-bulk-check) reads the *structured* event log, whose instrumentation for combat lifelink life-gain and death-watcher triggers (Fecundity-style) is still being completed under mtg-935 (Phase 2). Until that wiring lands, verify these event kinds with the watch command above; the assertions below document the intended contract.

[state]
turn=2
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=15
p0hand=
p0battlefield=Swamp; Swamp; Swamp; Fecundity; Vampire Nighthawk
p0library=Swamp; Swamp; Swamp
p0graveyard=
p0exile=

p1life=4
p1hand=
p1battlefield=Island; Island; Wind Drake
p1library=Island; Island; Island
p1graveyard=
p1exile=

[assertions]
# Deathtouch makes Nighthawk's 2 combat damage lethal: the blocking Wind Drake dies.
creature died Wind Drake
# Fecundity sees the death and its "whenever a creature dies" trigger fires.
trigger fired from Fecundity
# Nighthawk's lifelink gains P0 life equal to the combat damage it dealt (2).
life gained ge 2
